               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1569" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1569" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1569" type="surname" value="WOODDEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1569" type="given" value="SOPHIA"></interp>SOPHIA WOODDEN</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner lived with me for a month as a weekly servant. On the 12th of Aug. I put my purse behind my pillow—it con<lb></lb>tained seven sovereigns and a half—I missed them after breakfast next morning—she was very poor indeed when she came to me—I lent her 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on the Friday to buy a second-hand pair of shoes, as all her shoes were gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1570" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1570" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1570" type="surname" value="BRADLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1570" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BRADLEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable B</hi> 134.) I took the prisoner on the Friday following the robbery, and asked if she had got any money—she said she had none—she had a bonnet-box at her lodging, in Welborough-place, Chelsea—I found two boxes there, filled with good articles, which appeared to have been released from pawn, and in the large chest which she had not told me of, I found four sovereigns.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1571" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1571" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1571" type="surname" value="KNOWLES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1571" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH KNOWLES</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner came to lodge with me at Mrs. Foley's—I did not see her bring the boxes—I did not say that the boxes searched by the policeman, were brought there by her—I believe them to be hers.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1572" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1572" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1572" type="surname" value="ARNOLD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1572" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH ARNOLD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am searcher at the station. The prisoner told me the had got no money—I found on her 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—she asked me what would be done with her—I said I did not know—she said seven sovereigns and a half of the old lady's were lost, but they would not find the purse—if they went to her lodging they would find some money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1573" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1573" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1573" type="surname" value="GRAHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1573" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN GRAHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I was at Mr. Perkins's, the pawnbroker's, on the 16th of Aug.—I saw the prisoner there—she gave some tickets in—I saw her change a sovereign, and take two parcels out, and then I saw her give an<lb></lb>other sovereign.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had but one sovereign in my hand. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> You changed one, and when I came back you changed another—I said, "You have made a good harvest to leave the wash-tub."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I got four sovereigns at a raffle, and the rest I worked</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210206"></xptr>
               <p>hard for; on the Tuesday morning the prosecutrix sent me to the butcher's, to see if she had left her purse there.</p>
